## 📌 EIP-7782 Prysm Interop Audit [topic:65]

### ✅ Compare Lodestar EIP-7782 implementation vs prototyping notes + assess Prysm interop (done)
- **Source:** Nico, Telegram Lodestar WG topic #65, 2026-03-02 14:18 UTC (+ follow-up rerun request)
- **Status:** Done — reruns with exact blog-post pinned stack confirm issue is Prysm implementation gap, not config drift
- **Subtasks:**
  - ✅ Extract concrete requirements/assumptions from prototyping doc
  - ✅ Diff against Lodestar EIP-7782 branch behavior
  - ✅ Inspect Prysm for EIP-7782 support and config compatibility
  - ✅ Conclude static interop readiness + blockers
  - ✅ Spin up mixed Lodestar+Prysm EIP-7782 devnet
  - ✅ Observe finality/head/attestation behavior across fork boundary
  - ✅ Report whether interop works + exact divergence point (if any)
  - ✅ Run devnet with exact blog-post config and pinned versions (ethereum-package / Dora / Prysm images)
  - ✅ Run with Lodestar EIP-7782 image (local build) under same config
  - ✅ Compare outcomes and isolate whether failure is config drift vs Prysm implementation gap
- **Final result:**
  - **Prysm-only (exact blog config + pinned images):** healthy for hours, finality progressing, 6s slots active
  - **Mixed (same config + Lodestar image):** chain shares head pre-fork, then splits at/after slot 32
  - At divergence: Prysm remains on `current_version=0x70000038` (Fulu), Lodestar upgrades to `current_version=0xb0000038` (EIP-7782)
  - Prysm peers disconnect Lodestar peer ID; Lodestar logs `PublishError.NoPeersSubscribedToTopic` on post-fork block publication
  - Conclusion: Prysm needs an `UpgradeToEip7782` state transition hook to update fork version/fork digest at EIP-7782 fork epoch
- **Updates →** Telegram thread #65 in Lodestar WG

